# compare(_:)

**Instance Method**

Indicates the depth-first traversal order of the receiving index path and another index path.

## Declaration

```swift
func compare(_ otherObject: IndexPath) -> ComparisonResult
```

## Parameters

- **otherObject**: Index path to compare.

This value must not be `nil`. If the value is `nil`, the behavior is undefined.

## Return Value

The depth-first traversal ordering of the receiving index path and `indexPath`.

## Discussion

- [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedAscending]: The receiving index path comes before `indexPath`.
- [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedDescending]: The receiving index path comes after `indexPath`.
- [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedSame]: The receiving index path and `indexPath` are the same index path.
